  "I get on my computer and load up the files he wants, then I hit print.",
  "It’s about fifty pages’ worth of data, and I sit there, tapping my toes against the ground, watching the printer spit out each page.",
  "When the final page finishes printing, I yank out the sheets of paper and hurry over to his office.",
  "",
  "I crack open the door.",
  "“Mr. Lynch, sir?”",
  "",
  "“Come in, Nina.”",
  "",
  "I let the door swing the rest of the way open.",
